about you for a while.

731
00:51:20,995 --> 00:51:24,290
But fuck 'em, carv. You do what needs done.

732
00:52:08,334 --> 00:52:10,461
- I was out on one.
- You worked 8 to 4.

733
00:52:12,088 --> 00:52:14,924
I'm working a serial killer.
They call me on any suspicious death.

734
00:52:15,008 --> 00:52:16,384
Yeah? Where'd they reach you?

735
00:52:19,220 --> 00:52:22,890
Well, I'm not gonna lie. I... stopped,
had a couple, then I got the call.

736
00:52:22,974 --> 00:52:26,144
I know. I can smell the
Jameson's from here.

737
00:52:26,227 --> 00:52:28,104
Jamie and listerine, your scent.

738
00:52:28,187 --> 00:52:30,106
Beadie... I'm just...

739
00:52:30,189 --> 00:52:34,402
We had something, Jimmy.
You and me, we had something.

740
00:52:36,404 --> 00:52:40,658
When people told me stories about you,
about how you were,

741
00:52:40,742 --> 00:52:43,745
I couldn't believe it, I couldn't see it.

742
00:53:01,596 --> 00:53:02,597
Yeah.

743
00:53:03,639 --> 00:53:05,641
Yeah. 10 minutes.

744
00:53:06,351 --> 00:53:08,728
I got another one. South Baltimore.

745
00:53:13,274 --> 00:53:16,819
- Beadie, I'm chasing a serial killer.
- That's not all you're chasing.

746
00:53:19,447 --> 00:53:21,449
Look, if you don't want to be here...

747
00:53:23,451 --> 00:53:25,161
I got to go.

748
00:53:29,248 --> 00:53:31,417
He changed up.

749
00:53:31,501 --> 00:53:35,421
Marlo's no fool.
He know you be coming at him.

750
00:53:35,505 --> 00:53:37,757
Word is, him and Chris
went to the mattresses,

751
00:53:37,840 --> 00:53:39,717
on the move almost every night.

752
00:53:39,801 --> 00:53:42,887
- Fool enough to kick a sleeping dog.
- That should tell you something.

753
00:53:42,970 --> 00:53:46,349
I got the boy waiting on me,
I ain't go at him straight up.

754
00:53:46,432 --> 00:53:49,143
I go after his people, you feel me?
You hurt enough of them,

755
00:53:49,227 --> 00:53:51,854
that snake gonna stick his head
above that hole.

756
00:53:52,980 --> 00:53:55,066
That one there, you know him?

757
00:53:55,149 --> 00:53:56,317
He's a lieutenant.

758
00:53:56,401 --> 00:53:58,986
We gonna go after him first.

759
00:53:59,070 --> 00:54:01,155
Mark that ride, yo.

760
00:54:02,240 --> 00:54:03,574
Oscar.

761
00:54:04,450 --> 00:54:05,993
- Lester.
- Thank you, baby.

762
00:54:06,077 --> 00:54:08,079
- Anytime, man.
- Yeah. All right.

763
00:54:15,670 --> 00:54:18,756
He's perfect. Can't be dead
more than a couple of hours.

764
00:54:18,840 --> 00:54:20,508
Better lose these.

765
00:54:29,016 --> 00:54:31,102
You're a twisted fuck, mcnulty.

766
00:54:31,185 --> 00:54:32,895
Defense wounds. Help sell it.

767
00:54:34,313 --> 00:54:37,859
You got nerve calling me twisted.
You came up with the teeth.

768
00:54:38,860 --> 00:54:41,404
You know how these psycho
serial motherfuckers are.

769
00:54:41,487 --> 00:54:46,033
They mature. They start simple and crude

770
00:54:46,117 --> 00:54:49,620
and become more and more ornate.
There you go.

771
00:54:49,704 --> 00:54:52,248
Don't tell my mother or my priest
you saw me do this.

772
00:54:52,331 --> 00:54:53,833
Take it to my grave.

773
00:55:05,761 --> 00:55:08,014
- Want me to take that?
- Nah, I got it.

774
00:55:10,433 --> 00:55:13,352
What you see in this hole, man?
All the money you got?

775
00:55:16,063 --> 00:55:18,149
Your great-grandfather,

776
00:55:18,232 --> 00:55:21,444
first colored man to own his own house
in Johnson square.

777
00:55:22,361 --> 00:55:26,282
That means something,
something you young 'uns lost.

778
00:55:27,825 --> 00:55:30,203
Yeah. Well, we outside when you ready.

779
00:55:30,286 --> 00:55:33,498
Keep sharp while I'm gone, boy.
Charles say Omar back.

780
00:55:33,581 --> 00:55:34,749
He left Charles standing

781
00:55:34,832 --> 00:55:38,669
but he might feel less inclined
if he get the drop on you or yours.

782
00:55:39,170 --> 00:55:41,589
Ain't got to fret none about Omar.

783
00:55:48,763 --> 00:55:50,014
No need for that.

784
00:56:01,067 --> 00:56:03,027
You ain't come to see me off.

785
00:56:07,448 --> 00:56:08,616
My nephew.

786
00:56:13,287 --> 00:56:15,665
Boy was always a disappointment.

787
00:56:17,792 --> 00:56:19,377
But I treated you like a son.

788
00:56:20,002 --> 00:56:21,879
I wasn't made to play the son.

789
00:56:21,963 --> 00:56:23,839
But my supply - the good dope?

790
00:56:23,923 --> 00:56:26,467
The Greeks, they cool with it.

791
00:56:31,681 --> 00:56:33,474
Proposition, then.

792
00:56:34,934 --> 00:56:36,936
I just step out the way.

793
00:56:38,062 --> 00:56:40,898
You never hear from me again.
I just disappear.

794
00:56:40,982 --> 00:56:43,609
Joe, you'd be up into mischief in no time.

795
00:56:44,902 --> 00:56:47,572
Truth is, you wouldn't be able
to change up any more than me.

796
00:56:50,950 --> 00:56:52,201
Close your eyes.

797
00:56:55,288 --> 00:56:56,998
It won't hurt none.

798
00:56:59,208 --> 00:57:00,835
There. There, now.

799
00:57:02,920 --> 00:57:04,839
Joe, relax.

800
00:57:07,049 --> 00:57:08,634
Breathe easy.

